divs: Sighting DetailsWas outside my house in the garden with two friends watching the stars as it was a very very clear night when i noticed a dull orange oblong shaped object with wings moving very fast in the sky initially i thought it was a biplane but it was moving faster then expected of a biplane and there was no engine sound at all it looked to be fairly high up in the sky i instantly said "what the hell is that?" and my friends both saw it. it flew by for about 10-20 seconds and then disappeared.
trends: There have been 91 other sightings in London
There were no other sightings in London on or around May 23rd 2009
Summary: Dull orange coloured oblong object with wings flying fast in sky no sound.
